text: Location of Katsuta District in Okayama Prefecture is a district located in Okayama Prefecture, Japan. As of May 1, 2004, the population was 17,888. The area is 123.63 km². ==Towns and villages== *Nagi *Shōō ==History== Prior to February 28, Katsuta District consisted of: *Katsuta *Nagi *Shōboku *Shōō As of 2003, the district had an estimated population of 29,056 and a density of 113.58 persons per km². The total area was 255.82 km². *On February 28, 2005, Shōboku left Katsuta District and became part of the city of Tsuyama. *On March 31, 2005, Katsuta left Katsuta District and became part of the city of Mimasaka. title: Katsuta District, Okayama
